text: Neyriz County () is a county in Fars Province in Iran. The capital of the county is Neyriz. At the 2006 census, the county's population was 113,291, in about 35,000 families. The county is subdivided into four districts: the Central District, Abadeh Tashk District, Qatruyeh District, and Poshtkuh District. The county has four cities: Neyriz, Abadeh Tashk, Meshkan, and Qatruyeh. == References == * اطلس گیتاشناسی استان‌های ایران [Atlas Gitashenasi Ostanhai Iran] (Gitashenasi Province Atlas of Iran) Category:Neyriz County
